ile section, which appears to be where the basic settings are configured, including the design book layout.\n\nThe source mentions that when using Nablarch standards, only the file paths need modification while other settings remain unchanged, and the knowledge file reflects this accurately. Moving into the input design document configuration, there's a table of file path settings including the table definition, domain definition, code design, message design, and interface-related paths, all of which are present in the knowledge file.\n\nFor the file generation configuration section, I'm seeing the output directory and line separator options listed, though the knowledge file entry appears to be cut off.\n\nNow I'm checking the component definition file section and the input file reading settings, which includes configuration for adding columns and rows with index pairs and start row indices, plus notes about excluded sheets. The knowledge file covers all of this, and it also includes example configurations for reading message design documents, code design documents, table definitions, and external interface design documents, though that description seems to trail off.\n\nThe knowledge file mentions that domain definitions, validation processing definitions, and data type definitions use the same configuration items as message design documents, so those are omitted. I'm now verifying whether the knowledge file's additional elaboration about using the same class and property structure across component definition files constitutes a fabrication or just an expansion of what the source states. I'm noticing the knowledge file uses more specific terminology about \"class and property configuration\" than what's explicitly stated in the source text—it just says the settings are the same. Looking at the actual sentence in s9, it appears to be cut off mid-phrase, but the core issue is that the specific wording about DefinitionFileLoader and the technical details seem to be im